<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In determining the Host header, Zend_Http_Client assumes that HTTP (not HTTPS) is used when checking whether the default port is being used.  This means that HTTPS requests to port 443 will have the header Host: hostname.domain.com:443 instead of Host: hostname.domain.com.</p>

<p>I have seen one instance (<a href="https://records.txdps.state.tx.us/DPS_WEB/Sor/index.aspx?PageIndex=Search&amp;SubmitType=Address">https://records.txdps.state.tx.us/DPS_WEB/Sor/â€¦</a>) where including :443 in the Host header confuses the server and it returns a 404 Not Found error.  Although this is probably a bug in the web server (IIS) or web application, I am enclosing a patch that fixes this assumption and causes HTTPS requests to work with this site.</p>

    </div>
</div>

